    instruction: "You will have 20 minutes to plan, write and revise an essay about the topic below. Your response will be judged on how well you develop a position, organize your ideas, present supporting details, and control the elements of standard written English. You should write 200-300 words.",
    topic: "Obesity is a growing problem in many countries, placing a huge burden on healthcare systems. What are the causes of this, and what solutions can be proposed?",
    modelAnswer: "The obesity epidemic is one of the most pressing public health challenges of the 21st century. It is driven primarily by sedentary lifestyles and the availability of processed food. To resolve this, a combination of public education, taxation on unhealthy foods, and urban planning is required.\n\nThe rise in obesity correlates directly with modern convenience. Jobs have become sedentary, and leisure time is often spent in front of screens rather than outdoors. Simultaneously, the food industry has saturated the market with calorie-dense, nutrient-poor foods that are cheaper than healthy alternatives. This creates an environment where gaining weight is easy, and staying fit requires conscious, often expensive, effort.\n\nSolutions must address both diet and activity. Governments should implement a 'sugar tax' to make unhealthy snacks more expensive, using the revenue to subsidize fresh produce. Schools must prioritize physical education and teach nutrition as a core subject. Furthermore, cities should be designed to encourage walking and cycling, making physical activity a natural part of the daily commute rather than a chore.\n\nTo sum up, obesity is a complex issue born of modern lifestyle changes. However, by making healthy food affordable and physical activity accessible, societies can reverse this trend and relieve the pressure on healthcare systems.",
